      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "For individuals with curly or textured/kinky hair, it's essential to understand that they don't need to conform to the traditional, sleek look. Instead, they can focus on enhancing their natural texture while still presenting a polished, professional image. Using products that define curls and reduce frizz can help achieve a sleeker look. For example, a curl-defining cream or a light hold styling product can help enhance natural texture without looking too \"frosted\" or unnatural.\n\nHowever, it's also important to note that some textures, like tightly coiled hair, may require more maintenance to achieve a polished look. In these cases, using a diffuser or a curl-enhancing tool can help distribute heat evenly and reduce frizz. Ultimately, the goal is to find a balance between showcasing natural texture and presenting a professional image.",
